{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.14",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 14 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:1",
      "text": "Blessed is the man who has not slipped with his mouth, and doesn’t suffer from sorrow for sins.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:2",
      "text": "Blessed is he whose soul does not condemn him, and who has not given up hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:3",
      "text": "Riches are not appropriate for a stingy person. What would a miser do with money?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:4",
      "text": "He who gathers by denying himself gathers for others. Others will revel in his goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:5",
      "text": "If one is mean to himself, to whom will he be good? He won’t enjoy his possessions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:6",
      "text": "There is none more evil than he who is grudging to himself. This is a punishment for his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:7",
      "text": "Even if he does good, he does it in forgetfulness. In the end, he reveals his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:8",
      "text": "A miser is evil. He turns away and disregards souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:9",
      "text": "A covetous man’s eye is not satisfied with his portion. Wicked injustice dries up his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:10",
      "text": "A miser begrudges bread, and it is lacking at his table.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:11",
      "text": "My son, according to what you have, treat yourself well, and bring worthy offerings to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:12",
      "text": "Remember that death will not wait, and that the covenant of Hades hasn’t been shown to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:13",
      "text": "Do good to your friends before you die. According to your ability, reach out and give to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:14",
      "text": "Don’t deprive yourself of a good day. Don’t let your share of a desired good pass you by.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:15",
      "text": "Won’t you leave your labors to another, and your toils be divided by lot?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:16",
      "text": "Give, take, and treat yourself well, because there is no seeking of luxury in Hades.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:17",
      "text": "All flesh grows old like a garment, for the covenant from the beginning is, “You must die!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:18",
      "text": "Like the leaves flourishing on a thick tree, some it sheds, and some grow, so also are the generations of flesh and blood: one comes to an end and another is born.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:19",
      "text": "Every work rots and falls away, and its builder will depart with it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:20",
      "text": "Blessed is the man who meditates on wisdom, and who reasons by his understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:21",
      "text": "He who considers her ways in his heart will also have knowledge of her secrets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:22",
      "text": "Go after her like a hunter, and lie in wait in her paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:23",
      "text": "He who peers in at her windows will also listen at her doors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:24",
      "text": "He who lodges close to her house will also fasten a nail in her walls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:25",
      "text": "He will pitch his tent near at hand to her, and will lodge in a lodging where good things are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:26",
      "text": "He will set his children under her shelter, and will rest under her branches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.14.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:27",
      "text": "By her he will be covered from heat, and will lodge in her glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
